Mexico and shot up the town

00:17:42.040 --> 00:17:45.980
and killed some people and
so General Pershing went

00:17:45.980 --> 00:17:52.490
with General Patton as his
[inaudible] into Mexico

00:17:52.490 --> 00:17:55.350
which was a dress rehearsal
for World War I

00:17:55.350 --> 00:17:57.530
for the U.S. intervention
into World War I.

00:17:57.530 --> 00:18:03.780
On the other hand, to put in a
note, a positive note for a change,

00:18:03.780 --> 00:18:06.210
about the United States and
Mexico, if it hadn't been

00:18:06.210 --> 00:18:10.530
for Woodrow Wilson, Lord knows
what would have happened to Mexico

00:18:10.530 --> 00:18:14.750
because Woodrow Wilson
refused to accept [inaudible]

00:18:14.750 --> 00:18:20.880 position:56%
who was a conservative as president
because he had gotten the presidency

00:18:20.880 --> 00:18:25.550
through assassination
and thanks to his refusal

00:18:25.550 --> 00:18:27.760
to recognize [inaudible] fell

00:18:27.760 --> 00:18:34.590
and so Mexico became a
democratic state again,

00:18:34.590 --> 00:18:36.620
and it's really quite remarkable.

00:18:36.620 --> 00:18:39.020
Mexico is a very remarkable place.

00:18:39.020 --> 00:18:42.210
For example, and this is something
that people don't make enough hay

00:18:42.210 --> 00:18:48.160
about as far as I'm concerned,
in 1920 -- excuse me in 1829,

00:18:48.160 --> 00:18:52.050
President [inaudible]
abolished slavery in Mexico.

00:18:52.050 --> 00:18:57.210
