people walk in --

00:30:20.990 --> 00:30:22.760
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli: I
have a question for you.

00:30:22.760 --> 00:30:24.440
Do you know if it's true

00:30:24.440 --> 00:30:28.870
that Bernito Mussolini was
named after Benito Juarez?

00:30:28.870 --> 00:30:30.290
Have you ever heard this story?

00:30:30.290 --> 00:30:31.590
&gt;&gt; Barbara Tenenbaum: No.

00:30:31.590 --> 00:30:32.890
I don't think that's true.

00:30:32.890 --> 00:30:35.390
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli: His
parents were socialists and --

00:30:35.390 --> 00:30:38.220
I don't know, it's just I heard
this story, and I wondered if --

00:30:38.220 --> 00:30:39.530
&gt;&gt; Barbara Tenebaum: I'm going
to ask the Italian specialist.

00:30:39.530 --> 00:30:40.840
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli:
Okay, thank you.

00:30:40.840 --> 00:30:42.520
&gt;&gt; Talia Guzman Gonzalez: Is it
something you've heard then that --

00:30:42.520 --> 00:30:43.820
&gt;&gt; Barbara Tenenbaum:
I've never heard it.

00:30:43.820 --> 00:30:46.860
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli: I heard these
rumors, and I was just curious.

00:30:46.860 --> 00:30:48.160
&gt;&gt; Barbara Tenenbaum: I doubt it.

00:30:48.160 --> 00:30:50.890
But I will check on it for you.

00:30:50.890 --> 00:30:52.190
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli: Thank you.

00:30:52.190 --> 00:30:53.490
&gt;&gt; Talia Guzman Gonzalez:
Interesting.

00:30:53.490 --> 00:30:54.790
&gt;&gt; Barbara Tenenbaum:
You have to give me --

00:30:54.790 --> 00:30:56.090
did you give me your card?

00:30:56.090 --> 00:30:57.390
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli: I will.

00:30:57.390 --> 00:30:58.690
&gt;&gt; Talia Guzman Gonzalez: Do
we have any questions from --

00:30:58.690 --> 00:31:02.030
oh, there's one, one
all the way to the back.

00:31:02.030 --> 00:31:03.330
There's a microphone.

00:31:03.330 --> 00:31:05.970
&gt;&gt; Barbara Tenenbaum: I can't see.

00:31:08.080 --> 00:31:13.450
&gt;&gt; Do you have any comment about
Hollywood's version of Juarez,

00:31:13.450 --> 00:31:17.590
the film Juarez that was made
in 1930 starring Paul Mooney?

00:31:17.590 --> 00:31:21.960
And how inaccurate
or accurate was that?

00:31:21.960 --> 00:31:25.240
I know it wasn't based on
primary sources and everything,

00:31:25.240 --> 00:31:27.780
but the film Juarez
starring Paul Mooney.

00:31:27.780 --> 00:31:29.680
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli:
I haven't seen it.

00:31:29.680 --> 00:31:31.350
&gt;&gt; Barbara Tenenbaum:
I haven't seen it.

00:31:31.350 --> 00:31:34.290
&gt;&gt; Talia Guzman Gonzalez:
I haven't seen it.

00:31:34.290 --> 00:31:36.000
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli: I
heard, but I know the --

00:31:36.000 --> 00:31:40.690
we didn't see it for this.

00:31:40.690 --> 00:31:42.730
&gt;&gt; Barbara Tenenbaum: No.

00:31:42.730 --> 00:31:45.840
None of us have seen it.

00:31:45.840 --> 00:31:47.140
&gt;&gt; Talia Guzman Gonzalez: Sorry.

00:31:47.140 --> 00:31:48.440
Anyone else?

00:31:48.440 --> 00:31:50.740
Catalina?

00:31:58.120 --> 00:32:00.280
&gt;&gt; I'm curious about
where the scenes --

00:32:00.280 --> 00:32:03.250
the docudrama scenes are filmed.

00:32:03.250 --> 00:32:05.640
Did you guys go to Mexico
to the different places

00:32:05.640 --> 00:32:09.440
or did you have a set here?

00:32:09.440 --> 00:32:12.670
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli: Yeah,
I mean, we did most of them

00:32:12.670 --> 00:32:18.930
in the area close to the effect,
some of the colonial haciendas

00:32:18.930 --> 00:32:23.340
and for the desert sequence,
we went to which is not too far

00:32:23.340 --> 00:32:29.140
from Mexico City also,
Hidalgo and there is a couple

00:32:29.140 --> 00:32:31.120
of scene in the area of Pueblo.

00:32:31.120 --> 00:32:36.420
So [inaudible] is one, but
they were just around the --

00:32:36.420 --> 00:32:37.720
not to far from the effect.

00:32:37.720 --> 00:32:40.020
Yes.

00:32:48.050 --> 00:32:50.350
&gt;&gt; Talia Guzman Gonzalez:
Don't be shy.

00:32:53.070 --> 00:32:54.370
&gt;&gt; Thank you for your comments.

00:32:54.370 --> 00:32:58.240
Recognizing the Hispanic heritage
is not only Mexican heritage,

00:32:58.240 --> 00:33:02.310
is discovery planning other
Latin American countries films

00:33:02.310 --> 00:33:05.670
and documentaries and doc dramas?

00:33:05.670 --> 00:33:09.140
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli:
We would love to.

00:33:09.140 --> 00:33:11.140
We did a few.

00:33:11.140 --> 00:33:19.130
We did [inaudible], the
wife of [inaudible].

00:33:19.130 --> 00:33:24.650
We -- yeah we would love
to explore more characters.

00:33:24.650 --> 00:33:29.890
We will eventually I think.

00:33:29.890 --> 00:33:31.190
&gt;&gt; Talia Guzman Gonzalez:
There's audience for --

00:33:31.190 --> 00:33:32.490
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli: Yes, yes.

00:33:32.490 --> 00:33:33.790
&gt;&gt; Barbara Tenenbaum: Absolutely.

00:33:33.790 --> 00:33:35.090
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli: For sure.

00:33:35.090 --> 00:33:36.850
And there are countless stories
and countless characters.

00:33:36.850 --> 00:33:39.010
&gt;&gt; Barbara Tenenbaum: Definitely.

00:33:39.010 --> 00:33:41.080
&gt;&gt; Talia Guzman Gonzalez:
Well, I think this is it.

00:33:41.080 --> 00:33:46.230
Thank you so much, Michela, for the
wonderful film and for allowing us

00:33:46.230 --> 00:33:48.230
to show it here at the
Library of Congress.

00:33:48.230 --> 00:33:51.140
I'm sure we'll have people
come and ask questions.

00:33:51.140 --> 00:33:53.170
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli: We actually
would like to make a donation

00:33:53.170 --> 00:33:55.700
to the Library -- the
original script.

00:33:55.700 --> 00:33:57.290
&gt;&gt; Talia Guzman Gonzalez:
Oh wonderful.

00:33:57.290 --> 00:33:58.590
Fantastic.

00:33:58.590 --> 00:34:00.890
&gt;&gt; Michela Giorelli:
Of the docudrama.

00:34:04.280 --> 00:34:05.580
&gt;&gt; Talia Guzman Gonzalez:
That's great.

00:34:05.580 --> 00:34:07.380
Thank you.

